OVERVIEW
────────
Designed, deployed, and maintained a complete self-hosted operations
platform on a single Ubuntu server using Docker and open-source tools.
The platform provides real-time monitoring, centralized logging,
multi-layer security, automated backups, VPN access, and Git-based
configuration management.

INFRASTRUCTURE
──────────────
• Deployed and managed 10 Docker containers using Docker Compose
• Configured persistent volumes and custom bridge networking
• Built automated deployment scripts using Bash

MONITORING & OBSERVABILITY
──────────────────────────
• Prometheus    — Metrics collection every 15 seconds (6 targets)
• Grafana       — 4 custom dashboards (System, Docker, Logs, Overview)
• Loki          — Centralized log aggregation (5 log sources)
• Promtail      — Log shipping from system and Docker containers
• Node Exporter — Hardware-level metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network)
• cAdvisor      — Per-container resource monitoring
• Uptime Kuma   — Service uptime monitoring with alerting

SECURITY
────────
• UFW Firewall     — 15+ rules, default deny policy
• Fail2Ban         — Automatic IP banning after 3 failed SSH attempts
• WireGuard VPN    — Encrypted remote access tunnel (UDP 51820)
• SSH Hardening    — Key-only auth, root disabled, max 3 attempts,
                     custom banner, VERBOSE logging
• Authelia         — Single Sign-On (SSO) with MFA/TOTP support
• Auto Updates     — Unattended security patches via apt

BACKUP & RECOVERY
─────────────────
• Restic           — Encrypted automated daily backups (2 AM cron)
• Retention policy — 7 daily, 4 weekly, 3 monthly snapshots
• Scope            — Configs, Docker volumes, SSH, UFW, Fail2Ban rules
• Restore script   — Documented and tested recovery procedure

PLATFORM
────────
• Caddy            — Reverse proxy with custom HTML landing page
• Gitea            — Self-hosted private Git repository
• Version Control  — All configurations tracked in Git

